1
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:05,200
Who?

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,200
Dong Hwa's brother.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,333
Heo Dong Jin.

4
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:12,233
Darn you, why are you
playing such a sick joke?

5
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,533
What are you talking about?

6
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:18,133
Jeez, you're a lunatic.

7
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:20,467
Dong Jin died last year.

8
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:22,967
You've gone too far
with your jokes, you punk.

9
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:26,200
Don't you know
Dong Hwa's still messed up over that?

10
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:33,300
Did you see a ghost or something?

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,833
Who were you staying with?

12
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:45,167
Why haven't you reported anything?

13
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:47,333
What happened to Chu Tae Jeong?

14
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:48,733
I'm sorry.

15
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:52,867
He left the house this morning.

16
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:56,500
Is that so? Then why didn't you
report it immediately?

17
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:00,333
I was preoccupied
trying to find the cell phone. I'm sorry.

18
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:03,300
"Preoccupied"?

19
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:07,167
There wasn't anything else going on?

20
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:11,833
He's a cop after all.
You can't leave any room for him to doubt.

21
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:15,200
He'd come back with even an ounce of doubt.

22
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:21,433
If he does come back, what do I do?

23
00:01:21,433 --> 00:01:23,267
We have to kill him.

24
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:25,467
Isn't it obvious?

25
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:29,700
If he does come back,
it means he doubts who you really are.

26
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:33,700
Even though he's a cop,
we'll have no option but to get rid of him.

27
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,433
We need to finish this quickly,
so find the cell phone first.

28
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:39,500
Understood.

29
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,900
[Dong Hwa, I'm arriving soon.
I saw your brother. When are you returning?]

30
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:56,160
[Why aren't you replying?]

31
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,700
[But Dong Jin... Why is he so cute?
It makes me want to tease him.]

32
00:01:57,700 --> 00:02:00,500
[Dong Hwa, reply when you see this.
Nothing's wrong, right?]

33
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:08,867
[But Dong Jin... Why is he so cute?
It makes me want to tease him.]

34
00:02:08,867 --> 00:02:11,833
You're all right, aren't you?

35
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,567
Huh?

36
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,867
Anyway, I don't know why
you're making such sick jokes,

37
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:21,933
but let me know when you hear from Dong Hwa.

38
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:25,467
Chul Jin, we should head back now.

39
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:28,500
Tae Jeong, I have to go.

40
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,467
Let's talk more
when you come into work next week.

41
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:32,467
Oh, by the way,

42
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:34,633
don't go around stirring things up
in Dongcheon in the meantime.

43
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:38,233
You need solid evidence
to make a case, understand?

44
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:41,200
Forget about what happened 10 years ago.

45
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,900
I'm going now.

46
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,367
Are you Dong Jin?

47
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:49,533
No?

48
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:50,700
You're Dong Jin, right?

49
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,800
Are you really Dong Jin?

50
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,333
Where does Dong Hwa sleep?

51
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,333
What?

52
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:58,467
It seems like this house
only has one bedroom.

53
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:07,333
If he wasn't Dong Jin,
who in the world was he?

54
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:10,800
You wouldn't know the loneliness
of eating alone, would you?

55
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,933
I do.

56
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:15,400
How do you know?

57
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:19,433
When I was young,
I spent a lot of time alone too.

58
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,600
Investigate it thoroughly.

59
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,300
Huh?

60
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,533
You said it's important to you.

61
00:04:40,967 --> 00:04:43,000
Did you enjoy the smoke?

62
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:55,333
What? Still not ready to tell me?

63
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:03,167
Get up. Stop pretending.

64
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:16,967
Hey, Heo Dong Hwa.

65
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:18,667
Heo Dong Hwa!

66
00:05:26,688 --> 00:05:28,032
Darn it.

67
00:05:38,624 --> 00:05:40,064
Darn it.

68
00:05:53,856 --> 00:05:55,104
Darn it.

69
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:24,733
Gosh, where is it?

70
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:41,267
You shouldn't kill me yet.

71
00:07:06,767 --> 00:07:08,600
Chu Tae Jeong?

72
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,900
Dong Jin, you are home.

73
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,767
Yeah.

74
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,333
Dong Jin died last year.

75
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:19,000
Who were you staying with?

76
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,933
Anyway, what are you doing here?

77
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:28,167
I'm asking why you came back.

78
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,933
I was worried about you.

79
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:36,933
You were sick last night,

80
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:40,500
but I left without checking on you
in the morning.

81
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,267
I'm fine now.

82
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:47,600
If he does come back,
it means he doubts who you really are.

83
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:51,733
Even though he's a cop,
we'll have no option but to get rid of him.

84
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:57,767
By the way, you haven't heard from Dong Hwa?

85
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,567
No.

86
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:09,000
What were you doing?

87
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,000
Is something wrong?

88
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,000
Dong Jin.

89
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,900
I missed you.

90
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,533
You're going to stay here today, right?

91
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,800
Is that okay?

92
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,667
Are you going somewhere?

93
00:08:57,867 --> 00:09:00,300
I need to go take care of something.

94
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:02,000
Get some rest.

95
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:23,100
Spare me, please?

96
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:28,833
- Let me live. Please.
- Just tell me where the phone is.

97
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:32,567
You can't escape now.

98
00:09:32,567 --> 00:09:34,500
But if I tell you, you're going to kill me.

99
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:38,900
I can... I can help you quit that job, okay?

100
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:43,567
Enough money to live anywhere and never
have to work another day in your life...

101
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:46,367
I'll give that to you, okay?

102
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:51,833
Do you think you're in any position
to bargain with me?

103
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:54,767
Stop talking nonsense.

104
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,467
Tae Jeong's a cop.

105
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:02,300
He saw your face.
He also knows I disappeared.

106
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,133
At this rate,

107
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:06,633
it's only a matter of time
before you get caught.

108
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:10,067
Kill me. Kill me!

109
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:13,533
If you kill me, it'd only hurt you.

110
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:17,167
So, don't complicate things
any further and think carefully.

111
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,333
You want a fresh start too, don't you?

112
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,533
I said I will help you.

113
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,533
Why does he have so much cash?

114
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,667
Who is he really?

115
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:13,400
If you're not going to tell me
where the phone is, forget it.

116
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:19,200
Where are you going? Hey! Hey!

117
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,667
Gosh, darn it.

118
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:58,000
So, don't complicate things
any further and think carefully.

119
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,433
You want a fresh start too, don't you?

120
00:12:01,667 --> 00:12:03,700
You wait here.

121
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:06,000
I'll handle Min Ho myself.

122
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:23,267
Should we leave now?

123
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,967
Aren't you hungry?

124
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:30,367
No, I'm not very hungry yet.

125
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:32,367
How about some sushi?

126
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:34,633
You know Yukari in Cheongdam-dong?

127
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,867
A third-generation sushi chef
from Japan will be serving there

128
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:40,200
as a special guest chef for just one week.

129
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:44,033
Don't you want to go try it?

130
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,467
Sure. Should we go there then?

131
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:49,533
You and Min Ho...

132
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:53,667
are from the same orphanage, right?

133
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,867
How long have you known each other?

134
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:02,933
It's been about 15 years.

135
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:09,233
Are you feeling down
because an old friend died?

136
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,733
No, not at all.

137
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:14,233
Why do you think Min Ho died?

138
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:16,800
Because he failed to eliminate the target.

139
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:21,033
"Why couldn't he kill the target?"

140
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:23,267
I thought about it.

141
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:26,467
I think it was because he was a good person.

142
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:32,600
That's why he wanted to start fresh
with the woman he was supposed to kill.

143
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,767
How stupid.

144
00:13:34,767 --> 00:13:37,667
That target will come
to the Japanese restaurant.

145
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,900
You can handle it, right?

146
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:43,100
Yes.

147
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:45,400
Because you're different from Min Ho.

148
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:01,400
An art tube...

149
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,867
Why are you touching what's not yours?

150
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,500
I'm sorry.

151
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:41,600
I was curious what drawing tools you use.

152
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,400
It's quite heavy.

153
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:58,767
I guess you have a lot of tools.

154
00:15:03,467 --> 00:15:06,067
Can you draw me too?

155
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,633
What?

156
00:15:11,933 --> 00:15:14,067
Please draw me too.

157
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:27,900
I...

158
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:31,167
Can I move?

159
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,867
No.

160
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,733
But my body feels stiff.

161
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:41,533
That happens to everyone at first.

162
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:44,933
You'll be fine after some time passes.

163
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:48,400
I think it'd be okay
if I moved just a little.

164
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,200
Keep your gaze.

165
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,067
Don't look this way.

166
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,800
Are you nervous?

167
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,200
Your heart's racing, you know?

168
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,533
Maybe it's because your neck is slim.

169
00:16:08,233 --> 00:16:09,933
It makes it obvious.

170
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,733
Dong Jin.

171
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:23,633
Don't you miss Leo?

172
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:27,400
Who?

173
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:30,567
Leo. Your family's dog.

174
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:36,400
Oh yes, Leo.

175
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,700
When did Leo die?

176
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:44,933
I don't know. I don't remember.

177
00:16:52,567 --> 00:16:55,100
Can I ask you a question?

178
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,067
Who are you?

179
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,700
The dog that Dong Hwa's family raised

180
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,200
wasn't named Leo, but Logan.

181
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:19,733
Dong Jin personally named the dog.
There's no way he wouldn't know the name.

182
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:22,567
I heard Dong Jin died last year.

183
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:26,233
Didn't you know?

184
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:31,067
Who are you?

185
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:34,400
Why are you in this house?

186
00:17:53,367 --> 00:17:55,133
Then what about you?

187
00:17:57,433 --> 00:17:59,667
Why did you come back to this house?

188
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,333
Isn't this exactly the kind of thing
you can report to the police?

189
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:13,667
That someone's pretending
to be your friend's brother.

190
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:18,633
You're right.

191
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,933
I'm not Heo Dong Jin.
